def lss(x, s, e):
    if s + 1 < e:
        mid = (s + e) // 2
        l = lss(x, s, mid)
        r = lss(x, mid, e)
        i = l
        j = r
        while i < len(x) and j < len(x):
            if x[i] < x[j]:
                return r
            elif x[i] > x[j]:
                return l
            else:
                i += 1
                j += 1
        return l
    else:
        return s


class Solution:
    def lastSubstring(self, s: str) -> str:
        ans = lss(s, 0, len(s))
        return s[ans:]
